  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Humanitarian assistance to the most vulnerable people displaced by conflict in northern Iraq.</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">IDPs and host communities</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In Iraq Mercy Corps&#x2019; has established a flexible rapid response mechanism that allows for prompt distribution of NFI kits to meet IDP needs. Direct distribution will be selected in cases where the contents of packages match needs, where families are unable to access markets, where market prices have become very inflated, or where doing so would be burdensome or dangerous due to gender, security, or other concerns. Alternatively, Mercy Corps will support IDPs with an unconditional cash transfer (&#xA3;125 per household), which is appropriate when the target households have heterogeneous needs, remain highly mobile, and require assistance quickly in areas that are difficult to access. Specific activities will include:</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">SPECIFIC OBJECTIVE: Mercy Corps and local partners respond to immediate NFI and food needs of 21,600 most vulnerable displaced persons affected by the conflict.

 
 EXPECTED RESULTS:
  - 1,200 conflict-affected households (7,200 individuals) in northern Iraq have improved access to essential non-food items (kitchen sets) and food rations
  - 2,400 conflict-affected households (14,400 individuals) receive three rounds of unconditional cash assistance for a period of three months.</narrative>
  </description>
